## Testing Checklist

**WSL testing:**
- ✓ Basic functionality
- ✓ UI layout and rendering
- ✓ Unit and integration tests
- ✓ Rapid iteration during development

**Native Linux testing:**
- ✓ Multiple distributions (Ubuntu, Fedora, Arch)
- ✓ Different desktop environments (GNOME, KDE, XFCE)
- ✓ X11 and Wayland display servers
- ✓ Hardware acceleration
- ✓ Font rendering with complex scripts
- ✓ System theme integration
- ✓ Multi-monitor configurations
- ✓ HiDPI scaling
- ✓ Performance profiling

Use WSL for day-to-day development, but always validate on native Linux before release.

Getting your application into users' hands is just the beginning. A robust distribution and update strategy ensures users stay on the latest version with minimal friction.

## Distribution Channels

### Official Distribution Repositories

**Ubuntu PPA (Personal Package Archive):**
```bash
# Create Launchpad account and PPA
# Upload source package
dput ppa:yourusername/openmaui-app openmaui-app_1.0.0-1_source.changes

# Users install via:
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:yourusername/openmaui-app
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install openmaui-app
```

**Fedora COPR (Cool Other Package Repo):**
```bash
# Create COPR project at copr.fedorainfracloud.org
copr-cli create openmaui-app --chroot fedora-39-x86_64

# Build package
copr-cli build openmaui-app openmaui-app-1.0.0-1.src.rpm

# Users install via:
sudo dnf copr enable yourusername/openmaui-app
sudo dnf install openmaui-app
```

**Arch User Repository (AUR):**

Create `PKGBUILD`:
```bash
# Maintainer: Your Name <your.email@example.com>
pkgname=openmaui-app
pkgver=1.0.0
pkgrel=1
pkgdesc="OpenMaui Linux Application"
arch=('x86_64')
url="https://github.com/yourusername/openmaui-app"
license=('MIT')
depends=('dotnet-runtime' 'gtk3' 'webkit2gtk' 'harfbuzz')
makdepends=('dotnet-sdk')
source=("$pkgname-$pkgver.tar.gz::$url/archive/v$pkgver.tar.gz")
sha256sums=('SKIP')

build() {
    cd "$pkgname-$pkgver"
    dotnet publish -c Release -r linux-x64 --self-contained false -o out
}

package() {
    cd "$pkgname-$pkgver"
    install -dm755 "$pkgdir/usr/lib/$pkgname"
    cp -r out/* "$pkgdir/usr/lib/$pkgname/"

    install -Dm644 "openmaui-app.desktop" "$pkgdir/usr/share/applications/$pkgname.desktop"
    install -Dm644 "Resources/appicon.png" "$pkgdir/usr/share/icons/hicolor/256x256/apps/$pkgname.png"
}
```

