## Analytics and Telemetry

Track version adoption (with user consent):

```csharp
public class TelemetryService
{
    private const string TelemetryEndpoint = "https://telemetry.example.com/api/events";

    public async Task ReportAppStartAsync()
    {
        if (!HasUserConsent())
            return;

        var telemetry = new
        {
            EventType = "app_start",
            Version = Assembly.GetExecutingAssembly().GetName().Version.ToString(),
            OS = Environment.OSVersion.ToString(),
            Distribution = GetLinuxDistribution(),
            DesktopEnvironment = Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("XDG_CURRENT_DESKTOP"),
            DisplayServer = Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("XDG_SESSION_TYPE"),
            InstallationType = GetInstallationType(),
            Timestamp = DateTime.UtcNow
        };

        try
        {
            var json = JsonSerializer.Serialize(telemetry);
            var content = new StringContent(json, Encoding.UTF8, "application/json");
            await new HttpClient().PostAsync(TelemetryEndpoint, content);
        }
        catch
        {
            // Silently fail - telemetry should never break the app
        }
    }

    private string GetInstallationType()
    {
        if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("APPIMAGE")))
            return "AppImage";
        if (File.Exists("/.flatpak-info"))
            return "Flatpak";
        if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("SNAP")))
            return "Snap";
        if (File.Exists("/var/lib/dpkg/status"))
            return "Deb";
        if (File.Exists("/var/lib/rpm"))
            return "RPM";

        return "Unknown";
    }

    private string GetLinuxDistribution()
    {
        try
        {
            var osRelease = File.ReadAllLines("/etc/os-release")
                .Select(line => line.Split('='))
                .Where(parts => parts.Length == 2)
                .ToDictionary(parts => parts[0], parts => parts[1].Trim('"'));

            return osRelease.GetValueOrDefault("PRETTY_NAME", "Unknown");
        }
        catch
        {
            return "Unknown";
        }
    }

    private bool HasUserConsent()
    {
        // Check if user has consented to telemetry
        return Preferences.Get("telemetry_enabled", false);
    }
}
```

## Release Checklist

Before each release:

- ✅ All tests passing (unit, integration, manual)
- ✅ Version numbers updated (.csproj, changelog, manifests)
- ✅ Release notes written
- ✅ Packages built for all formats (.deb, .rpm, Flatpak, AppImage)
- ✅ Packages tested on clean VMs
- ✅ Code signing completed
- ✅ Git tag created and pushed
- ✅ GitHub/GitLab release created with artifacts
- ✅ Distribution repositories updated (PPA, COPR, AUR)
- ✅ Flathub pull request submitted (if applicable)
- ✅ Documentation updated
- ✅ Social media/blog announcement prepared

A well-executed distribution strategy ensures your OpenMaui application reaches users across the diverse Linux ecosystem while maintaining quality and reliability.
